8:
Yes. All idols cow-ntracted with a
Cosmic Beast emit a kind of glowing
energy.
11:
We were tracking Noenne by the
trail she left behind...
13:
When suddenly we were suspended
midair, and found ourselves
transported to your village.
17:
I searched through many
coordinates, but I couldn't locate
your home world.
25:
So it looks like we're stranded for the
time being.
31:
It's all right. We're here through no
mis-steak of yours.
35:
Sorry to keep you waiting, guys. I
tried my best to sneak away, but the
work just wouldn't stop piling on.
39:
Nah, we're the ones who should be
apologizing, barging in when you're
so busy.
42:
That's okay. I could actually use a
breather like this.
46:
You're Beaucy, right? I heard you
came from the same world as
Noenne and her friends.
51:
Cacow! BRASS, loading complete!
No escaping from—
57:
Whoa, hold your cow! The idols here
don't compete through fisticuffs!
62:
Is that so? I simply reacted on
instinct when I sensed her idol
power level.
69:
Diva Media. Noenne informed me
about you, but to see how truly
powerful you are without the
blessing of a Cosmic Beast...
72:
You shine just as bright as BRASS
idols, despite your lack of Cosmic
Energy.
77:
I'll... take that as a compliment, I
guess?
81:
And you, Rec Register. I've heard
much about you as well, including
how you wrote Noenne's music.
85:
Please, I simply made a few
arrangements. If you're in the
business of producing music, I'd be
happy to help.
89:
That's all right. A gravure idol like me
has no need for personalized
moo-sic.
92:
I don't dance or sing. I simply display
my body and let the masses come
to me.
95:
How fascinating. In other words,
your body itself is sacred and
worthy of being worshipped.
99:
To me, the idols of your world are
fascinating. I am drawn to them like
a cattle to hay.
105:
Well... If you're interested, I'm
actually supposed to go on a
concert tour next week.
108:
Regis, you can grab a few reserved
seats, right?
114:
Of course. Your wish is my
command.
134: She was amazing. What a show.
137:
Yeah, it's totally different from just
listening to her normally. Being in an
actual stadium turns up the hype to
eleven.
153:
Idols from another world aren't to be
underestimated.
...I stan.
156:
Perhaps I need to adjust my
schedule for sealing away idols.
162:
Why are you so intent on ending
idols forever? Do you hate them that
much?
167:
Not at all. In fact, I absolutely adore
them. Idols are to mankind what
wagyu is to beef.
173:
Which is exactly why I'll never forgive
the BRASS for utilizing them as
instruments of war.
175:
Nor can I forgive the idols that stood
by and allowed it to happen. They
were in the wrong. All of them.
178: So I will seal it all away.
186:
If it's just the BRASS you want to end,
surely there are other ways to go
about this.
190:
I'm afraid that's impossible. Idols will
always be drawn to Cosmic Beasts.
As long as idols exist, the BRASS will
return.
192:
Even Dia, as unlikely as the
possibility might be, could one day
be contracted to a Cosmic Beast.
194:
Surely you also recognize how
wrong it is for idols to be forced to
fight one another.
198:
Regis would definitely blow his
circuit board if he heard about it...
204:
S-still, if you truly love idols as much
as you say you do... In your heart of
hearts, you can't possibly want to
seal them away forever.
213:
I will see this through. For my own
sake.
222:
That's enough about this subject. If
you'll excuse me, I need to milk this
opportunity for all it's worth.
225:
Please check the box next to the
merchandise you want to order in
your catalogue. Make sure to enter
your ticket number as well.
227:
Thank you very mooch. Hmm, you
can buy a maximum of one of each
item. Well, I've got to have the
pamphlet—
238:
Ah! The limited edition light sticks
are sold out?! I was too late...
243:
Forget love, she's OBSESSED with
idols!
246:
Somehow, I get the feeling she'll do
the right thing.
